repos.name: handlebars-helper-aggregate
repos.description: {{aggregate}} handlebars helper. inlines content from multiple files optionally using wildcard (globbing/minimatch) patterns. uses YAML front matter as context for each file. optionally pass in a sorting function.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-autolink
repos.description: {{autolink}} handlebars helper. Generate relative links from the "current page" to other dest pages.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-br
repos.description:
{{br}} Handlebars helper. Adds `
` tags to generated HTML. Great for prototyping.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-compose
repos.description: {{compose}} handlebars helper. Similar to {{aggregate}}, but this is a block helper that extends the inner block's content with content from "external" files, while also extending the context with YAML front matter from those files. You may also optionally use wildcard (glob/minimatch) patterns.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-condense
repos.description: Remove extra newlines from HTML content.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-datetime
repos.description: Handlebars helper for adding RFC-822 formatted datetimes to XML feeds

repos.name: handlebars-helper-disqus
repos.description: {{disqus}} Handlebars helper. Simplifies adding [Disqus](https://disqus.com/) comments to your site.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-eachitems
repos.description: {{eachItems}} handlebars helper.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-feed
repos.description: Handlebars helper for generating entries for RSS or atom feeds.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-ghbtns
repos.description: {{ghbtn}} handlebars helper. Add github buttons (http://ghbtns.com) to your site.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-include
repos.description: Handlebars helper, alternative to built-in partials. Similar to handlebars-helper-partial, but this helper will allow wildcard (glob) patterns. Like Assemble itself, this helper will automatically determine the correct context to use, or a context may be explicitly passed in as a second parameter.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-isActive
repos.description: {{isactive}} handlebars helper. Adds an 'active' class to the 'current page'. Class can be customized.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-jade
repos.description: {{jade}} handlebars helper, for converting basic Jade templates to HTML.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-less
repos.description: {{less}} handlebars helper. This helper allows you to use LESS inside style tags in your HTML. By default, the resulting CSS will be rendered inside the `<style>...</style>` tags of the rendered HTML, but you may alternatively define a destination path using the `dest` hash option of the helper.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-lorem
repos.description: {{lorem}} handlebars helper, for generating lorem lorem placeholder text.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-md
repos.description: A new and improved {{md}] helper! Convert markdown to HTML. Use wildcard (glob) patterns for files. Like Assemble itself, this helper will automatically determine the correct context to use, or a context may be explicitly passed in as a second parameter.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-minify
repos.description: {{minify}} handlebars helper, for minification of HTML with html-minifier.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-moment
repos.description: {{moment}} handlebars helper. Combines the powers of Assemble, Handlebars.js and Moment.js into a great helper to master time.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-not
repos.description: {{not}} handlebars helper. Conditionally render a block if the condition is false. This block helper is really just a semantic alternative to {{isnt}}

repos.name: handlebars-helper-paginate
repos.description: {{paginate}} handlebars helper. Made for Assemble, the static site generator for Node.js, Grunt.js and Yeoman.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-partial
repos.description: Handlebars helper, alternative to built-in partials. Like Assemble itself, this helper will automatically determine the correct context to use, or a context may be explicitly passed in as a second parameter.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-pkg
repos.description: {{pkg}} handlebars helper, for retrieving a value from your project's package.json

repos.name: handlebars-helper-post
repos.description: {{post}} handlebars helper, for including a post, or a list of posts.

repos.name: handlebars-helper-prettify
repos.description: {{prettify}} handlebars helper, for formatting ("beautifying") HTML, CSS and JavaScript.

repos.description: {{process}} handlebars helper, for processing raw templates in included content, with the correct context
